In this article, it is stated that President Obama spoke with President Abbas of the Palestinian Authority to congratulate him on the start of Israeli-Palestinian proximity talks. President Obama expressed his support for the establishment of an independent Palestinian state living in peace and security with Israel. The need for both parties to negotiate seriously and in good faith was discussed, with the goal of moving from proximity talks to direct negotiations as soon as possible to reach an agreement on permanent status issues. President Obama also appreciated President Abbas' recent outreach to the Israeli people and urged him to prevent acts of incitement or delegitimization of Israel. The President confirmed his intention to hold both sides accountable for actions that undermine trust during the talks and expressed his anticipation of receiving President Abbas at the White House soon.